From an early age, it was clear that Blind Tom possessed extraordinary musical
gifts. He could imitate, either vocally or musically, any sound he heard. This,
coupled with an encyclopedic memory and all-encompassing passion for music,
meant that by the age of sixteen, he hovered somewhere between a respected
concert pianist and glorified sideshow freak.

