"Each consonant has an inherent vowel which is usually short 'a' (in Bengali,
and Assamese, it is short 'ô' due to sound shifts). Other vowels are written by
adding to the character. A mark, known in Sanskrit as a virama/halant can be
used to indicate the absence of an inherent vowel."

